phrase.item: Mee dangkis noe oo.
I have a story (lit: one of my stories)
Awin oo.
Yes, oh!
Dangkis noe yaa Naan.
My story is about Naan (God).
Naan lap mat ji.
Naan married his wife.
Mop tongɗok koe mat ji.
He was (sitting) together with his wife.
Bak zap.
He had children.
Mop bak zap, mop bak zap.
They had children, they had children.
Yakal zoe laa mee laa, mat nyi gam ak.
(So) They gave birth to one child, his wife was/got pregnant.
Zoe laa mee laa, laa koe mis.
They had a/another child, the child was a male.
Mat nyi toe laa, lala jee laa koe mis.
When his wife gave birth, that child was a male child.
Lala je, mop toe pes sem nyi, gok!
That child, if they name him, he would get sick.
Gap mut.
He would faint (lit: he cut death).
Mop toe pes sem nyi, gok!
When they gave him a name, he got sick
gap mut.
and fainted.
Ani mop yin:
Then they said:
De tong noehoe ɓoe, nwaa yit nyi a noehoe, not sem.
if it is so, they should leave him like that, without a name.
Lala je toe mwakal kom ɓoe, mop pes sem nyi.
If the child grows up "before", they will give himself name.
Lala mwakal, baa noekoes, mop lwe pes sem, mop pes sem nyi ma.
(As) the child grew up, they did not give him a name.
Lala bom son.
The child began to mature (lit: touch wisdom?)
Zoe son lat ɓoe yin jin kan ji poe sem ji nkaa shin boe ji.
When he finished maturing, he said he would be the person to name himself.
Pes sem ji boe ji, mop yong gurum mop zoe tong weet.
(When) he named himself, they called people and they all came and sat down.
Moenan mop zoe tong.
The elders came and sat down.
Mop yin: To!
They said: "Okay!
Lala je hoe gwaar kan... yin a jin kan ji pes sem nkaa shin boe ji.
This child here says he will be the person to give himself name."
Yakal pes sem ji, sem ji a Enkoemalong.
Then he named himself, (saying) his name is Enkoemalong (lit: the thought that passes/is beyond a king).
Jin Enkoemalong Naan.
"I am E. (son) of Naan."
Moenan mop koeling weet.
The elders heard everything.
Mop yin: sem nyi a Enkoemalong.
they said his name his Enkoemalong.
Mop yikoel weet zu mop man sem nyi a Enkoemalong Naan.
They all left knowing that his name is Enkoemalong of Naan.
Mwaan noekoen, mwaan noekoen, mwaan, mwaan, mwaan, mwaan.
Life went on. (?lit: go there, go there, go, go, go, go).
Laa zoe ... zoe mwakal.
The child came and grew.
Kwanyi lap mat ji.
As for him, he married (lit: collected) his wife,
Yakal pet loe ji.
and made his house
Naan mang... Ndaa nyi Naan mang gwaar a gurum, gwaar a laa koe bis.
Good considered... His father, God, considered "You are a bad (person...) child.
Laa koe ji pes sem nyi gwaar yin:
You, the child that I gave name to, (you) said that
Jin ji pes sem ma oo ɓoe a nyi lala nyi pes sem kaa shin boe ji,
I (the father) should not give a name, but it is he, the child, he will give himself a name.
gwaar lala koe bis.
you are a bad child."
Zoe mwakal ji lap mat ji pet lang loe ji,
He grew up, married his wife and made his house.
toe pet lang loe ji na nyi.
After he made his house
Naan poe bakal nyi, nyi poe tukup nyi poe saan koe nyi.
Naan (God) was setting a trap for him, his heart (lit: liver) is burning for him [i.e., he is angry with him].
A noekoen min ɓoe,
After that,
toe mop ɗel maar mwos,
they were going to farm for alcohol
mop toe soek mwos, mop toe ɗel maar mwos,
they soaked alcohol and went to the farm for alochol,
gurum mop yikoel weet, mop ɗel maar mwos poe tungloe.
All the people got up and went to farm for alcohol in their clan.
Naan, mee ɓit ɓoe naan yakal yin...
Naan (God), one day, Naan then said...
Naan shin wukaam
Naan prepared a way
de nyi toe nyi lala na nyi
to kill him, that child.
gwaar a laa koe bis
"You are a bad child."
tang nyi poe tang de toe doe.
He wanted (he was looking) to kill him.
Lala maa koe tok nyi.
(But) The child is wiser than him.
Yakal mop pwat mee ɓit ɓoe
And they came out one day,
Naan soek mwos.
Naan prepared alcohol.
Soek mwos ɓoe yong gurum mop meet meet meet meet meet.
(When) He prepared alcohol, he called all kinds of different people.
Mop zoe kang weet koelaap Naan,
They all came together in Naan's house
koe lala nyi naa nyi, yakal yong lala nyi naa nyi Enkoemalong.
along with his child... he also called his child Enkoemalong.
Zoe noekoen weet,
(They) all came there.
mop zoe tong noekoen koe pee mwos,
They came and sat there where there was alcohol,
mop shwaa mwos,
they drank the alcohol,
mop shwaa mwos noekoen loe goelang,
they drank alcohol inside the sitting room,
mop tong noekoen loe goelang,
They sat inside the sitting room,
mop shwaa mwos, mop shwaa mwos, mop shwaa mwos,
they drank alcohol, they drank alcohol, they drank alcohol,
waba mempee wul nang ɓoe Naan yin:
until it reached some point and Naan said:
Gurum mop nwaa pwat weet,
"People, you should all go out,
de zun kan zu shin kang zun koe lala ji.
so we will meet/discuss, I and my child."
Noekoen tong koedee lala Enkoemalong man,
There the child Enkoemalong already knew
Naan mwaanɗok poe shin mbii noekoen de ji de kan tang wukaam de kan toe jin.
Naan was (going about) doing things for him to find a way to kill him.
Lala yong hak.
The child (had) called squirrel.
Toe yong hak, yin:
When he called squirrel, he said:
hak gwaar ok pee nɗoekoen koelaap ji,
"Squirrel, you should dig a place inside my house.
nɗoekoen loe ji.
inside my room.
Noekoen yil, yil, yil, yil, yil ɓoe sai pee koe
There, down, down, down, down, down (up to) the place where
waba pee koe mop kan tong shwaa mwos pee loe Naan dee yit.
as far as the place where they will sit and drink alcohol in Naan's room.
Lala ok naam hak ok fung
The child dug, and squirrel also dug a hole.
ɗal noekoen yil dukum pet noekoen loe goelang, poe loe goelang Naan.
it went like that underground, and (went and) came out there in the sitting room, through the door of the sitting room of Naan,
pee koe mop tong kwat shwaa mwos yi.
sit to drink alchohol, then God said to the people
To, Naan noekoen kenan Naan yakal yin:
Now, Naan was there, and he said.
Nwaa gurum, nwaa pwat.
"You people, you should go out."
Kop gurum mop pwat weet ɓoe ɗee mop ɗee mop koe yem ji.
The rest of the people all went out; he remained, together with his son.
Mop toe pwat noekoen gbang ɓoe
After they had gone out,
yin, yakal pet to ɓoe yin jin waa.
he said... then he went out and said "I am coming."
Pet poe koeɓang gbang ɓoe pet mang wus lang koe loe
He went outside and set fire to the house.
yaa poe loe hokot ɓoe mang wus lang koe loe
He closed the door, then set fire to the house
koe lala tongɗok nɗoekoen mee shin nɗoekoen loe goelang mop dee, loe goelang nyi Naan.
where the child was sitting inside alone, inside the sitting room, they remained in his sitting room, Naan's.
Noekoen bang wus ɓoe
From there (only?) fire,
ɗe gurum mop lap wurang ɓoe oo,
and the people were shouting: Oh!
wus toe loe oo, wus toe loe oo, wus toe loe oo, wus toe loe oo!
Fire is burning the house, oo! Fire is burning the house, oo! Fire is burning the house, oo! Fire is burning the house, oo!
Lala ɗeeɗok noekoen.
The child is there.
Kwa nyi Naan mang yin, wus toe lala nyi nɗoekoen loe koey.
As for him, Naan thought the first had already burnt the child, he being inside the house.
Son koe lala nyin shin koey koe hak ok pee ndee,
The wisdom that the child has previously done already with squrrel to dig a hole,
lala yakal koeroekoe kpuruk, nɗoekoen fung hak ndee
The child then entered sharply inside the squirrel's hole
ɓoe goe goe pet goe goe waa,
and you, you went out, and you, you go,
goe waroe a fung fung fung ɓoe dukum pet ji koelap ji.
and you enter hole, hole, hole, and come out to his house.
Yakal kaa loe moelang.
Then he climbed upstairs.
Loe shik a loe moelang dok kuɗyit a loe moelang mop toe.
The house was an upstairs one in the past, is has been said.
Loe poe nyi ɗakaa koe tok.
He put its door upward.
Tong gbang mop kat lala langɗok
Suddenly, they saw the child on top/hanging.
puren koe kaa loe ji ɓoe yakal kwa nyi poe lap wurang
there on his roof, and he was shouting
noekoen koelaap ji kwal yin
there at his home, saying that:
Wus toe ndaa,
Fire killed father,
wus toe loe ndaa Naan oo,
Fire burned the house of my father, Naan, oo!
wus toe loe ndaa Naan oo,
Fire burned the house of my father, Naan, oo!
wus toe loe ndaa Naan oo.
Fire burned the house of my father, Naan, oo!
Loe wurang
He shouted
yin: Wus toe loe ndaa Naan,
that: Fire burned the house of my father, Naan, oo!
wus toe loe ndaa Naan oo, wururu.
Fire burned the house of my father, Naan, oo! Wururu!
Naan yin tong gbang ɓoe a yin...
Naan said just like that, and I said
Gurum yakal ɗel fii fii mop:
The people (who) went were surprised:
Gwaar shin nang ɓoe gwaar waa dukum pet waa baa koelaap gwaar koey nɗoekoen wus?
"How did you manage to get out and arrive already in your own house inside the fire?"
Naan ɗoek kaa ji.
Naan nodded his head.
Kwa nyi ɗoek kaa ji zak.
As for him (the child), he nodded his head also.
Mbii koe de kan ji shin koedat dee hoe?
"What will I do now?
Kwa jin kan ji soek mwos.
As for me, I will prepare alcohol."
Kwa nyi soek mwos zak.
As for him, he prepared alcohol also.
Kwa nyi soek mwos zak.
As for him, he prepared alcohol also.
Kwa nyi soek mwos.
As for him, he prepared alcohol.
Yong...:
He invited...
Gurum mop zoe weet zak yit
All the people came again also.
Gurum mop wul.
The people came.
Mop wul a nyi ɓoe, mop zoe tong loe goelang nyi.
They arrived and came sat in his sitting room.
Naan kwa nyi yakal yong noemot, lyak moen ji a koe noemot,
Naan called frog, and told his own to frog.
yin: Noemot paa zoe ok pee njin.
saying: "Frog, you should come and dig a hole for me."
Noemot zoe ok pee.
Frog came and dug a place.
Lala je tongɗok ji loe.
That child was sitting in the room.
Lala je mwaanɗok poe shwaa mwos, toe shwaa mwos ɓoe
The child was continuing drinking alcohol and when he drank alcohol
toe kwan kas nyi nfung noekoen pee,
he would discard the residue in the hole there in the place,
fung dee de hak
that hole for squirrel.
tongɗok noekoen de toe kwan doe ɓoe hak
sitting there so that when he poured it, then squirrel
toe shwaa nyi ɓoe poe doe hak toe shwaa.
would drink it, then he gave the squirrel to drink.
Naan kwa nyi yakal mwaanɗok poe yong noemot de zoe ok pee moen nyi.
Naan, as for him, he was continuing calling frog to come dig a place of his own.
par koe lala yong mop der ze shuwa mos ko zak
that when the child call him he will do the same also
koelap ji zak tto noemot yi ok peh yi lani deet
then the frog dug hole just for him and his children only
poe mwan koe yin koe zap yi la ni tukap doe mwan
then the frog dug small hole and enter inside with his children
tong doe noekoen deh naan toe shuwa mos doe toe
and when God drink alchohol, he will
kwan a kas mus ni boelep ko ni ok peh deh ekoes ni
pour the chaff inside the hole for the frog
bal yi lala yakal goe shin ka mini naan zak ga yin
then the child repeat as he did
gurum mop pwat gurum mop yikil pwat wet
and said to the people that they should all go out
yakal yin kan zu shin tong koe ndah ji naan ko ni
for him to have meeting with his father
boe yakal pet mang wus lang koe loe naan deh
then he went outside and set fire on the building
noekoen zak ko ni nah yin dok noemot ok peh kai
his fahter is thinking that the hole is big enough
deh kan ji yakal ji re noekoen zak deh wa ze
for him to enter inside also
ji dugum kah mini koe nin shin deh yi noekoen
he went out as he did before
bang boe wus lang koe loe gurum mop loe wuran
he then set fire and assigned people to shout
gurum mop loe wuran gurum mop loe wuran wus toe loeh
people shouted fire, fire
wus toe loe enkoemahlong oh wus toe loe enkoemahlong
fire burn enkoemahlong's house
oh noekoen naan yakal der re fung noemot noemot
then God enter frog's hole
der re fung fung noekoen mah yakal lyak koe noemot
as he want to enter, there was no hole, then he said to frog
kwal yin noemot yi poe peh noemot toe lap yin
frog, allow me to enter, frog answered and said
yeh mwan koe zap noe noemot noemot noemot yi
no way, the hole is for me and my children
poe peh noemot yin peh mwan koe mun koe zap noe
allow me frog, but the hole is for me and my children
mah wus toeh naan noekoen mop koe matd ji
God and his wife were burnt with fire
wus toe mop noekoen mop pwat noekoen vokom
then they were all blind
noekoen pet noekoen boe naan ko ni yin kah pet
and God said I will go out, he then come out
pet pus matd ko ni vokom pet ko ni pet boe taar
his wife was also blind, then she came out inside moon
ani boe mop mun map yin koe nah taar boe nah nih
from there our people say if you see moon very well
dong dong boe ka goe kot la kakak la membi lang ka
you will see it with something inside
la kakak wus koe toeh matd ni deh
the fire that burn his wife
toe neh pus dong dong ka boe kat la kakak lang dak
and if you see sun very well, you will see something
noekoen a kakak koe wus dok toeh ni naan deh
that was burn by fire
taar a matd mis nya pus doe
moon is a female while sun is a male
dankis noe kurkutug
this is the end of my story
